OL,4,Cmanifesto booklet more accessible
OL,6,FHowever, changes have been ruled out
OL,7,Ffor the upcoming election, with the
OL,8,Fdecision left up to individual
OL,9,Fcandidates to ensure their manifestos
OL,10,Fare easy to read ahead of the booklet
OL,11,Fbeing printed.
OL,13,FDeputy Carl Meerveld, President of
OL,14,FGuernsey's States Assembly and
OL,15,FConstitution Committee, says: "Each
OL,16,Fcandidate has the power to choose
OL,17,Ftheir own format.
