OL,4,Cmanifesto booklet more accessible
OL,6,FInstead, they can cast up to thirty-
OL,7,Feight votes for anyone who is standing
OL,8,Fto become a deputy.
OL,10,FThis has led to the States delivering
OL,11,Fa candidate manifesto to every
OL,12,Fhousehold ahead of the poll to decide
OL,13,Fwho to vote for, with nominations
OL,14,Fclosing at 4:30pm on Wednesday 14 May.
OL,16,FThe Election itself will take place on
OL,17,FWednesday 18 June and islanders must
OL,18,Fregister to vote by midnight on
OL,19,FWednesday 30 April.
